[07/04/2024, 11:06:17] Michael Dos Santos: Instituto Superior T√©cnico Lisboa (IST)

Advantages:

Top Ranked: IST is consistently ranked the top university in Portugal and highly regarded in Europe for engineering and technology (https://www.timeshighereducation.com/world-university-rankings/instituto-superior-tecnico-lisboa).
Strong Industry Connections: IST boasts strong ties to major tech companies, offering internship and research opportunities.
Research Focus: The program emphasizes research and innovation, fostering a strong foundation for further studies or research careers.
Disadvantages:

Competitive: Admission to IST is highly competitive, with high entrance requirements.
Language: Instruction is primarily in Portuguese, although English courses are available.
Cost: Tuition fees at IST may be higher compared to US.
University of Seville (US)

Advantages:

Affordable: Tuition fees at US are generally lower than at IST.
Spanish Language: Studying in Spanish can be a benefit if you plan to work in Spanish-speaking countries.
Cultural Experience: Seville offers a vibrant and historic city life.
Disadvantages:

Ranking: US may not rank as high as IST in computer science programs.
Industry Network: Industry connections might be less extensive compared to IST.
Research Focus: The program might have a stronger emphasis on coursework compared to research at IST.
Additional factors to consider:

Your language proficiency: If you're comfortable with Portuguese, IST offers a clear academic advantage.
Career Goals: If you aim for research or a career in Portugal, IST could be a better fit. For Spanish-speaking countries, US might be more relevant.
Campus Life: Consider the city atmosphere and student life you prefer.
Recommendation:

If your primary focus is on a highly ranked program with strong industry connections and research opportunities, and you're comfortable learning Portuguese, IST might be the better choice. However, if affordability, Spanish language learning, and a vibrant city life are your priorities, the University of Seville could be a good option.
